A vintage 1960s scientific illustration style image showing an elegant wooden card catalog cabinet with multiple open drawers, each drawer containing colorful index cards organized into cascading layers and nested folders. The cards fan out in a spiral pattern, revealing hierarchical organization with tabs of different colors representing categories within categories. A magnifying glass hovers over one section, revealing even finer subdivisions. The background features a warm sepia-toned library setting with soft directional lighting casting long shadows. The composition emphasizes depth and the satisfying visual rhythm of organized information branching from broad categories into specific details, like a tree's root system made of paper and wood.
